{
  "texts": [
    "Using Botometer for all the 1.4M users is difficult and costly due to the API limit.",
    "Instead, we extract users with more than five tweets in our dataset (127,547 users) to mitigate the impacts of the active bots.",
    "Using a score of 0.43 as a threshold following [46], a relatively conservative setting among previous literature [47], we regard 13,315 (10.4%) users as bots and remove their 872,893 tweets.In total, we obtain 3,065,972 tweets and 1,082,092 users.",
    "We denote these generative AI-related tweets as T genAI in the rest of the paper.",
    "The final number of tweets for each generative AI tool is displayed in Table 1."
  ]
}